Suspected armed robbers numbering ten attacked some passengers travelling along the Lokoja-Abuja Federal Highway on Sunday evening. Tribune Online reliably gathered that several vehicles ran into them as luck, however, ran out on some who got killed. A source who was at the scene of the incident said the armed robbers blocked the highway with stones and other dangerous objects to prevent the motorists from escaping from the trap. However, when some motorists travelling along the highway got to the scene, they could not escape as the bandits opened fire on the passengers. Some of them died and others sustained different degrees of injuries. Review of Tribal Leadership Workers’ remittances largest inflow on balance-of-payments… 10 mistakes leaders make when giving performance feedback Brand focus: La Casera, boosting CSR profile through… ALSO READ: Anglican Communion bans brochure, ‘asoebi’ uniform during burials The incident which took place after Gadder beau, before Kweita, a community along Lokoja-Abuja Federal Highway. The eyewitness report said a team of military men, however, ran into the accident and helped to convey the corpses to the hospital. The eyewitness report could not immediately ascertain the actual number of people feared dead, and efforts to reach the Police and Road safety the number of casualties has been difficult. Meanwhile, all effort to speak with the Police Public Relation Officer of Kogi State Police Command, William Ayah on the incident proved abortive. However, a top Police officer who is not authorised to speak on the matter told Tribune Online said the Police Commissioner, CP Hakeem Busari has drafted some armed policemen and detective to the area. SHOCKING LIFE STORY!!! Abuja Man reveals (FREE) secret Fruits that Increased his Manh0d size and Lasting Power in just 7days… CLICK HERE
